The presence of the deep-water flathead Bembradium roseum Gilbert, 1905 (family Plectrogeniidae) from the northeastern Indian Ocean is reported for the first time. The species was previously known from the Pacific Ocean, from the central eastern Indian Ocean off Lombok (Indonesia), from the Ninety East Ridge in the central Indian Ocean, and was recently recorded from northwestern Madagascar.
identifiedBy: Aneesh Kumar KV (CMLRE) and Sileesh M (KUFOS)
